<quantity box="[1365,1462,1638,1662]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="130" pageNumber="243" unit="m" value="17.5" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="10.0">10–25 m</quantity>
, dead (Dijkstra &amp; Moolenbeek, 2008: 19). Maximum depth range of live-taken specimens is 
<quantity box="[1180,1275,1697,1721]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="130" pageNumber="243" unit="m" value="15.0" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="12.0">
12– 
<specimenCount box="[1221,1275,1697,1721]" pageId="130" pageNumber="243" type="generic">18 m</specimenCount>
</quantity>
. Present specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[894,992,1726,1750]" name="Australia" pageId="130" pageNumber="243">Australia</collectingCountry>
