.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="131" lastPageNumber="244" pageId="130" pageNumber="243" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="130.[838,1468,1772,2001]" pageId="130" pageNumber="243">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[839,945,1772,1796]" pageId="130" pageNumber="243">Remarks</emphasis>
. The epithet “limatula” (Latin, diminutive of “lima”, a file) is an indeclinable noun. The present specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[896,994,1830,1854]" name="Australia" pageId="130" pageNumber="243">Australia</collectingCountry>
are indistinguishable from the 
<typeStatus box="[1326,1423,1830,1854]" pageId="130" pageNumber="243">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="130.[838,1468,1772,2001]" lastBlockId="131.[119,750,152,293]" lastPageId="131" lastPageNumber="244" pageId="130" pageNumber="243">
<bibRefCitation author="Wagner, H" box="[869,1066,1859,1884]" pageId="130" pageNumber="243" pagination="86" refId="ref321084" refString="Wagner, H. P. 1982. Notes on type material of the family Pectinidae (Mollusca: Bivalvia). 1. Pecten limatula Reeve, 1853, a new synonym of Chlamys irregularis (Sowerby, 1842). Basteria 46: 86." type="journal article" year="1982">Wagner (1982: 86)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized the present species with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Sowerby, 1842)" baseAuthorityName="G. B. Sowerby II" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[839,1284,1889,1913]" class="Bivalvia" family="Pectinidae" genus="Laevichlamys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pectinida" pageId="130" pageNumber="243" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="irregularis">
<emphasis box="[839,1102,1889,1913]" italics="true" pageId="130" pageNumber="243">Laevichlamys irregularis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sowerby II, G" box="[1117,1277,1889,1913]" pageId="130" pageNumber="243" pagination="45 - 82" refId="ref318986" refString="Sowerby II, G. B. 1842. Monograph of the genus Pecten. In Thesaurus Conchyliorum, or Figures and Descriptions of Shells, part 2, pp. 45 - 82, pls 12 - 20 [also labelled Pecten pls 1 - 11]. London: G. B. Sowerby." type="book chapter" year="1842">Sowerby, 1842</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName authority="(Reeve, 1853)" baseAuthorityName="Reeve" baseAuthorityYear="1853" class="Bivalvia" family="Pectinidae" genus="Laevichlamys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pectinida" pageId="130" pageNumber="243" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="cuneata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="130" pageNumber="243">Laevichlamys cuneata</emphasis>
(Reeve, 1853)
</taxonomicName>
, above), and considered that there are no significant morphological differences between the two nominal taxa. However, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Reeve" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[1091,1205,1977,2001]" class="Bivalvia" family="Pectinidae" genus="Laevichlamys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pectinida" pageId="130" pageNumber="243" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="limatula">
<emphasis box="[1091,1205,1977,2001]" italics="true" pageId="130" pageNumber="243">L. limatula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has much finer and more evenly arranged radial sculpture than 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Reeve" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[518,629,152,175]" class="Bivalvia" family="Pectinidae" genus="Laevichlamys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pectinida" pageId="131" pageNumber="244" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="cuneata">
<emphasis box="[518,629,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="131" pageNumber="244">L. cuneata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which has much more unevenly spaced and less well-developed narrow and broad radial costae. Moreover, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Reeve" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[496,612,210,234]" class="Bivalvia" family="Pectinidae" genus="Laevichlamys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pectinida" pageId="131" pageNumber="244" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="limatula">
<emphasis box="[496,612,210,234]" italics="true" pageId="131" pageNumber="244">L. limatula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is smaller in size, relatively thin, and more brightly coloured. 
<bibRefCitation author="Waller, T" pageId="131" pageNumber="244" pagination="195 - 249" refId="ref321508" refString="Waller, T. R. 1993. The evolution of &quot; Chlamys &quot; (Mollusca: Bivalvia: Pectinidae) in the tropical western Atlantic and eastern Pacific. American Malacological Bulletin 10: 195 - 249." type="journal article" year="1993">Waller (1993: 204)</bibRefCitation>
placed both species in his new genus 
<emphasis box="[566,718,269,293]" italics="true" pageId="131" pageNumber="244">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Waller" authorityYear="1993" box="[566,714,269,293]" class="Bivalvia" family="Pectinidae" genus="Laevichlamys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pectinida" pageId="131" pageNumber="244" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Laevichlamys</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
